{
  "chapter": {
    "id": "web:philemon.1",
    "translationId": "web",
    "bookSlug": "philemon",
    "chapterNumber": 1,
    "referenceLabel": "Philemon 1",
    "summary": "Source text for Philemon 1 in World English Bible."
  },
  "verses": [
    {
      "id": "web:philemon.1.1",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "philemon",
      "chapterNumber": 1,
      "verseNumber": 1,
      "referenceLabel": "Philemon 1:1",
      "text": "Paul, a prisoner of Christ Jesus, and Timothy our brother, to Philemon, our beloved fellow worker,",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "web:philemon.1.2",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "philemon",
      "chapterNumber": 1,
      "verseNumber": 2,
      "referenceLabel": "Philemon 1:2",
      "text": "to the beloved Apphia, to Archippus our fellow soldier, and to the assembly in your house:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:philemon.1.3",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "philemon",
      "chapterNumber": 1,
      "verseNumber": 3,
      "referenceLabel": "Philemon 1:3",
      "text": "Grace to you and peace from God our Father and the Lord Jesus Christ.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:philemon.1.4",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "philemon",
      "chapterNumber": 1,
      "verseNumber": 4,
      "referenceLabel": "Philemon 1:4",
      "text": "I thank my God always, making mention of you in my prayers,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:philemon.1.5",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "philemon",
      "chapterNumber": 1,
      "verseNumber": 5,
      "referenceLabel": "Philemon 1:5",
      "text": "hearing of your love and of the faith which you have toward the Lord Jesus and toward all the saints,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:philemon.1.6",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "philemon",
      "chapterNumber": 1,
      "verseNumber": 6,
      "referenceLabel": "Philemon 1:6",
      "text": "that the fellowship of your faith may become effective in the knowledge of every good thing which is in us in Christ Jesus.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:philemon.1.7",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "philemon",
      "chapterNumber": 1,
      "verseNumber": 7,
      "referenceLabel": "Philemon 1:7",
      "text": "For we have much joy and comfort in your love, because the hearts of the saints have been refreshed through you, brother.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:philemon.1.8",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "philemon",
      "chapterNumber": 1,
      "verseNumber": 8,
      "referenceLabel": "Philemon 1:8",
      "text": "Therefore though I have all boldness in Christ to command you that which is appropriate,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:philemon.1.9",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "philemon",
      "chapterNumber": 1,
      "verseNumber": 9,
      "referenceLabel": "Philemon 1:9",
      "text": "yet for love’s sake I rather appeal to you, being such a one as Paul, the aged, but also a prisoner of Jesus Christ.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:philemon.1.10",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "philemon",
      "chapterNumber": 1,
      "verseNumber": 10,
      "referenceLabel": "Philemon 1:10",
      "text": "I appeal to you for my child Onesimus, whom I have become the father of in my chains,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:philemon.1.11",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "philemon",
      "chapterNumber": 1,
      "verseNumber": 11,
      "referenceLabel": "Philemon 1:11",
      "text": "who once was useless to you, but now is useful to you and to me.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:philemon.1.12",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "philemon",
      "chapterNumber": 1,
      "verseNumber": 12,
      "referenceLabel": "Philemon 1:12",
      "text": "I am sending him back. Therefore receive him, that is, my own heart,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:philemon.1.13",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "philemon",
      "chapterNumber": 1,
      "verseNumber": 13,
      "referenceLabel": "Philemon 1:13",
      "text": "whom I desired to keep with me, that on your behalf he might serve me in my chains for the Good News.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:philemon.1.14",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "philemon",
      "chapterNumber": 1,
      "verseNumber": 14,
      "referenceLabel": "Philemon 1:14",
      "text": "But I was willing to do nothing without your consent, that your goodness would not be as of necessity, but of free will.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:philemon.1.15",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "philemon",
      "chapterNumber": 1,
      "verseNumber": 15,
      "referenceLabel": "Philemon 1:15",
      "text": "For perhaps he was therefore separated from you for a while that you would have him forever,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:philemon.1.16",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "philemon",
      "chapterNumber": 1,
      "verseNumber": 16,
      "referenceLabel": "Philemon 1:16",
      "text": "no longer as a slave, but more than a slave, a beloved brother— especially to me, but how much rather to you, both in the flesh and in the Lord.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:philemon.1.17",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "philemon",
      "chapterNumber": 1,
      "verseNumber": 17,
      "referenceLabel": "Philemon 1:17",
      "text": "If then you count me a partner, receive him as you would receive me.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:philemon.1.18",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "philemon",
      "chapterNumber": 1,
      "verseNumber": 18,
      "referenceLabel": "Philemon 1:18",
      "text": "But if he has wronged you at all or owes you anything, put that to my account.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:philemon.1.19",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "philemon",
      "chapterNumber": 1,
      "verseNumber": 19,
      "referenceLabel": "Philemon 1:19",
      "text": "I, Paul, write this with my own hand: I will repay it (not to mention to you that you owe to me even your own self besides).",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:philemon.1.20",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "philemon",
      "chapterNumber": 1,
      "verseNumber": 20,
      "referenceLabel": "Philemon 1:20",
      "text": "Yes, brother, let me have joy from you in the Lord. Refresh my heart in the Lord.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:philemon.1.21",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "philemon",
      "chapterNumber": 1,
      "verseNumber": 21,
      "referenceLabel": "Philemon 1:21",
      "text": "Having confidence in your obedience, I write to you, knowing that you will do even beyond what I say.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:philemon.1.22",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "philemon",
      "chapterNumber": 1,
      "verseNumber": 22,
      "referenceLabel": "Philemon 1:22",
      "text": "Also, prepare a guest room for me, for I hope that through your prayers I will be restored to you.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:philemon.1.23",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "philemon",
      "chapterNumber": 1,
      "verseNumber": 23,
      "referenceLabel": "Philemon 1:23",
      "text": "Epaphras, my fellow prisoner in Christ Jesus, greets you,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:philemon.1.24",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "philemon",
      "chapterNumber": 1,
      "verseNumber": 24,
      "referenceLabel": "Philemon 1:24",
      "text": "as do Mark, Aristarchus, Demas, and Luke, my fellow workers.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:philemon.1.25",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "philemon",
      "chapterNumber": 1,
      "verseNumber": 25,
      "referenceLabel": "Philemon 1:25",
      "text": "The grace of our Lord Jesus Christ be with your spirit. Amen.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    }
  ]
}
